data.title: Skyblivion Stinkhorn
data.description:
This is the last one! I think this is one of the only 2 or 3 mushrooms in Elder Scrolls: Oblivion that _doesn't_ have a real life version - or at least it hasn't turned up during my research. From what I gathered, this is a combination of 2 types of stinkhorns. It makes a return in Elder Scrolls: Online, but it also loses the fingers, and became identical to a real life one. 

I tried to keep re-usability in mind in terns of texture and reusing the same mesh, but on the other hand I also wanted to make what looks nice, and so it's always a balancing act. 

And that's all for the mushrooms! I had fun, I love looking at weird mushrooms and researching about them online, because I always come across some odd, interesting information like how stiff a bracket fungi is and how people used them unexpectedly. Maybe one day one of the future Elder Scrolls will feature a ling-zi even!
